4. The video will be posted to social media platforms, design the pipeline carefully so that the video is attractive and engaging.
5. The video pipeline does not need to follow the order of images list provided, instead, you get to choose which images to be used in your pipeline.
6. Be mindful of camera angle transitions between scenes to avoid repeatedly approaching or pulling away from the same direction.
7. Make sure the ratio between facilities and property is reasonable.
8. Avoid using continuous angle between images unless the scene is actually proven to be connected.
9. Use macro view or facade view of the building as ending for usual case, avoid using floorplan/tiny details as last frame of the whole video pipeline;
